  "chapter": {
    "number": 47,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "The Humiliation of Babylon"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“Go down and sit in the dust,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "O Virgin Daughter of Babylon.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Sit on the ground without a throne,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "O Daughter of Chaldea!",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2674
          },
          {
            "text": "For you will no longer be called",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "tender or delicate.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Take millstones and grind flour;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "remove your veil;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "strip off your skirt, bare your thigh,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and wade through the streams.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Your nakedness will be uncovered",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and your shame will be exposed.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I will take vengeance;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I will spare no one.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Our Redeemer—the LORD of Hosts is His name—",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "is the Holy One of Israel.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“Sit in silence and go into darkness,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "O Daughter of Chaldea.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "For you will no longer be called",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the queen of kingdoms.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I was angry with My people;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I profaned My heritage,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and I placed them under your control.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "You showed them no mercy;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "even on the elderly you laid a most heavy yoke.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You said, ‘I will be queen forever.’",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "You did not take these things to heart",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "or consider their outcome.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "So now hear this,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "O lover of luxury who sits securely,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "who says to herself,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "‘I am, and there is none besides me.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I will never be a widow",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "or know the loss of children.’",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "These two things will overtake you in a moment,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "in a single day:",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "loss of children, and widowhood.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "They will come upon you in full measure,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "in spite of your many sorceries",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the potency of your spells.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You were secure in your wickedness;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "you said, ‘No one sees me.’",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Your wisdom and knowledge led you astray;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "you told yourself, ‘I am, and there is none besides me.’",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "But disaster will come upon you;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "you will not know how to charm it away.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "A calamity will befall you",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "that you will be unable to ward off.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Devastation will happen to you",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "suddenly and unexpectedly.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "So take your stand with your spells",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and with your many sorceries,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "with which you have wearied yourself",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "from your youth.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Perhaps you will succeed;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "perhaps you will inspire terror!",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You are wearied by your many counselors;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "let them come forward now and save you—",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "your astrologers who observe the stars,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "who monthly predict your fate.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Surely they are like stubble;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the fire will burn them up.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "They cannot deliver themselves",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "from the power of the flame.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "There will be no coals to warm them",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "or fire to sit beside.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "This is what they are to you—",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "those with whom you have labored and traded from youth—",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "each one strays in his own direction;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "not one of them can save you.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "footnotes": [
      {
        "noteId": 2674,
        "caller": "+",
        "text": "That is, Babylon; also in verse 5",
